v8:item.v8:content: The list of objects that are registered for sending to another application but cannot be exported due to some issues.

When sending data to another application, some of the infobase objects were found that are registered in the data exchange but cannot be exported due to some issues. To fix this, open each object and eliminate the issues. This list will be updated at the next attempt to send the objects to another application.

Settings.QueryText: SELECT ALLOWED DataExchangeResults.ObjectWithIssue AS Ref, CASE WHEN DataExchangeResults.DeletionMark THEN 2 ELSE 0 END AS DeletionMark, DataExchangeResults.DocumentNumber AS DocumentNumber, DataExchangeResults.DocumentDate AS DocumentDate, DataExchangeResults.InfobaseNode, DataExchangeResults.OccurrenceDate, DataExchangeResults.Cause, DataExchangeResults.IsSkipped, VALUETYPE(DataExchangeResults.ObjectWithIssue) AS TypeAsString FROM InformationRegister.DataExchangeResults AS DataExchangeResults WHERE DataExchangeResults.IssueType = VALUE(Enum.DataExchangeIssuesTypes.UnpostedDocument)

SELECT ALLOWED DataExchangeResults.ObjectWithIssue AS Ref, CASE WHEN DataExchangeResults.DeletionMark THEN 4 ELSE 3 END AS DeletionMark, DataExchangeResults.InfobaseNode, DataExchangeResults.OccurrenceDate, DataExchangeResults.Cause, DataExchangeResults.IsSkipped, VALUETYPE(DataExchangeResults.ObjectWithIssue) AS TypeAsString FROM InformationRegister.DataExchangeResults AS DataExchangeResults WHERE DataExchangeResults.IssueType = VALUE(Enum.DataExchangeIssuesTypes.BlankAttributes)
SELECT NULL AS Date, NULL AS Ref, NULL AS TypeAsString, NULL AS ThisVersionNumber, NULL AS OtherVersionNumber, NULL AS OtherVersionAuthor, NULL AS OtherVersionAccepted, NULL AS VersionIgnored
